<p><strong>Trieste bookcase </strong>is a clear example of Enzo Mari’s <strong>research for materials and simplicity</strong>. He combines beauty and functionality, two elements that a design project like Trieste must have in order to be appealing and useful inside a house or office. Talking about its technical features, Trieste is a wall-mount bookcase system with steel shelves, sides and uprights epoxy painted in opaque white or pearl grey. It can be extended and modernised to fit everyone’s need. Its structure is solid and stable, as Mari says: “When I create a project I always want it to last for at least 100 years or even 1000 years.”</p>

